{"id":"0811.3138","submitter":"Tae-Suk Kim","authors":"Tae-Suk Kim, Hyun-Woo Lee, B. C. Lee","title":"Nonlocal Spin Transport in Lateral Spin Valves with Multiple\n  Ferromagnetic Electrodes","comments":"6 pages, 1 figure","journal-ref":"J. Kor. Phys. Soc. 53, 973 (2008)","doi":"10.3938/jkps.53.973","report-no":null,"categories":"cond-mat.mtrl-sci cond-mat.mes-hall","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We study the nonlocal spin transport in a lateral spin valve with multiple\nferromagnetic (FM) electrodes. When two current-injecting and two spin\ncurrent-detecting electrodes are all ferromagnetic, the number of possible\nnonlocal spin signal states is four at maximum. In reality, this number is\nreduced, depending on the inter-probe distance and the relative magnitudes of\nthe spin resistances. Our theoretical results are in agreement with recent\nexperiments of spin injection into an Al island, a carbon nanotube, and\ngraphene.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 19 Nov 2008 15:29:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-13"}
